criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  The patient age 18 Years to 76 Years;

          -  Fewer than 6 months from onset of TAO;

          -  Clinical diagnosis of Graves' disease associated with active TAO and a clinical
             activity score of ≥ 3;

          -  Moderate to severe TAO;

          -  No previous medical or surgical treatment, excluding local supportive measures and
             oral steroids if the maximum cumulative dose is less than 1000 mg methylprednisolone
             or equivalent with at least 6 weeks between last administration of oral steroids and
             randomization.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Optic neuropathy, severe orbital appearance and surgical;

          -  Extra-thyroid disease;

          -  Pregnant and children;

          -  Severe impairment of cardiac, hepatic and renal functions;

          -  Allergies;

          -  Other contraindications.
